import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True, color='blue', label='Size Distribution')
    plt.axvline(data['size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['size'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of sizes in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('parent')['size'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='parent', y='size', data=data_grouped)
    plt.title('What is the average size of items in each parent category?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Parent Category')
    plt.ylabel('Average Size')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Parent Categories', loc='upper right', labels=data_grouped['parent'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    names = data['name'].values
    text = ' '.join(names)
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', colormap='viridis').generate(text)

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the most common name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    specific_name = 'example_name'  # Replace 'example_name' with the specific name you want to filter by
    filtered_data = data[data['name'] == specific_name]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=filtered_data, x='size', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.axvline(filtered_data['size'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {filtered_data['size'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title('What is the distribution of sizes for items with a specific name?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
